<section id="rt2001">
  <p align="left">
    <font face="verdana" size="13" color="#000000">One of the most common areas of mistakes is the use and omission of the articles 'a', 'an' and 'the'. You need to decide whether or not one is necessary, and, if it is, which one. Similarly, you have to take care to make appropriate use of possessive adjectives (my, your, his, her, its, our, their). The next two exercises will give you practice in both of these.</font>
  </p>
